{
  "stem": "20405.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But every week, we were going-- every Friday, I remember-- we were going to go to the Jewish synagogue in Athens and to give a presence to the German, because we had a card over there, that we are present.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Every week we supposed to go there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So, the underground over there, they was telling us to stay going over there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "If anything happened, they going to help us not to let them-- the Germans to get us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's why Dario and me and my brother, we were going every week to the synagogue-- just to have time, the rest of the week, to do something, to send, maybe, Jewish guy who needed to go to-- to send them to the partisans on the mountain, and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Who is Dario?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Dario, his name is Dario-- or David, actually-- Gabbai.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We two were friend, even with the family, we were friends and going to school together all the times.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew-- we know each other since we were-- since our childhood.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "With Dario, we-- we-- our parents are like cousins, from his grandmother and my grandmother sisters.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In every neighborhood was under-- was this kind of a collaborator they call him, or something of the young Greeks, which they didn't want the Germans.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because the Germans were killing, almost every day, Greek people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't want to know about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- we became-- we had some relationship with the underground.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because many people of the underground were coming down in the city and talking to the head of this organization, calling EAM, to give some informations, what's going on, and so on, and what to do.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we never saw them.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
